tderr","text":"Epoch 04:   0%|                                                  | 0/1284 [00:00<?, ?it/s]","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Ep 03 (1456s) | cls=0.3352  reg=0.3874  reid=0.2261\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"Epoch 05:   0%|                                                  | 0/1284 [00:00<?, ?it/s]","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stdout","text":"  Ep 04 (1455s) | cls=0.3331  reg=0.3900  reid=0.2199\n","output_type":"stream"},{"name":"stderr","text":"Epoch 05:  85%|████████████████████████████████▉      | 1086/1284 [20:33<03:39,  1.11s/it]","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def load_model(backbone_name, loss_type, weight_path, device):\n    model = build_model(backbone_name=backbone_name, loss_type=loss_type,\n                        pretrained=False).to(device)\n    ckpt = torch.load(weight_path, map_location=device, weights_only=False)\n    model.load_state_dict(ckpt[\"model\"])\n    model.eval()\n    return model, ckpt.get(\"loss_log\", [])\n\nmodel_baseline, log_baseline = load_model(\n    \"resnet50\", \"oim\", \"weights_baseline.pt\", DEVICE)\nmodel_resnet18, log_resnet18 = load_model(\n    \"resnet18\", \"oim\", \"weights_resnet18.pt\", DEVICE)\nmodel_triplet, log_triplet = load_model(\n    \"resnet50\", \"triplet\", \"weights_triplet.pt\", DEVICE)\n\nprint(\"All models loaded\")","metadata":{"_uuid":"4e10a17a-62af-4ecc-a675-d8b1b1899087","_cell_guid":"d39f749d-8e10-432c-abd0-e2265ce898e3","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 6. Training Curves\n\nThese plots show how the losses evolve during training. I track three components: classification loss (person vs. background), box regression loss, and the Re-ID loss (OIM or triplet). All values were logged by wandb during training; here I also reconstruct them from the saved loss logs for convenience.","metadata":{"_uuid":"8f0b5ee1-8bc6-4f39-aa9f-9775e09d8739","_cell_guid":"bde4f3cc-9050-4059-92d1-6845d0fec47f","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def plot_loss_curves(logs, keys=(\"loss_cls\", \"loss_box_reg\", \"loss_reid\")):\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, len(keys), figsize=(5 * len(keys), 4))\n    colors = {\"Baseline (R50+OIM)\": \"#4C72B0\",\n              \"Ablation A (R18+OIM)\": \"#DD8452\",\n              \"Ablation B (R50+Tri)\": \"#55A868\"}\n\n    for ax, key in zip(axes, keys):\n        for name, log in logs.items():\n            if not log:\n                continue\n            vals = [e.get(key, 0.0) for e in log]\n            ax.plot(range(1, len(vals) + 1), vals, label=name,\n                    color=colors.get(name), linewidth=2)\n        ax.set_title(key.replace(\"loss_\", \"Loss: \"))\n        ax.set_xlabel(\"Epoch\")\n        ax.legend(fontsize=8)\n        ax.grid(alpha=0.3)\n\n    plt.tight_layout()\n    plt.savefig(\"training_curves.png\", dpi=120, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\nall_logs = {\n    \"Baseline (R50+OIM)\": log_baseline,\n    \"Ablation A (R18+OIM)\": log_resnet18,\n    \"Ablation B (R50+Tri)\": log_triplet,\n}\nplot_loss_curves(all_logs)","metadata":{"_uuid":"e7612e9d-9c8a-474a-89ca-8bbee65ccff9","_cell_guid":"fa7782a8-9bc8-4ab9-915c-f56f75d7f0bd","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 7. Feature Extraction\n\nTo evaluate, I need to:\n1. Run the detector on every test frame and collect detections + Re-ID embeddings (gallery).\n2. Extract an embedding for each of the 2,057 query crops.\n\nThen matching is done by cosine similarity between query and gallery embeddings.","metadata":{"_uuid":"15d2843e-ace0-417b-b43b-acf4998e64e9","_cell_guid":"06e45ade-07cf-4c4f-9bcf-95523db10fb8","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"eval_transform = T.Compose([T.ToTensor()])\n\ntest_ds_eval = PRWGalleryDataset(DATASET_ROOT, split=\"test\",\n                                  transform=eval_transform)\nquery_ds_eval = PRWQueryDataset(DATASET_ROOT, transform=eval_transform)\n\nprint(\"Extracting features for Baseline...\")\ngallery_dets_base, gallery_feats_base = extract_gallery_features(\n    model_baseline, test_ds_eval, DEVICE)\nquery_feats_base = extract_query_features(\n    model_baseline, query_ds_eval, DEVICE)\n\nprint(\"Extracting features for Ablation A...\")\ngallery_dets_r18, gallery_feats_r18 = extract_gallery_features(\n    model_resnet18, test_ds_eval, DEVICE)\nquery_feats_r18 = extract_query_features(\n    model_resnet18, query_ds_eval, DEVICE)\n\nprint(\"Extracting features for Ablation B...\")\ngallery_dets_tri, gallery_feats_tri = extract_gallery_features(\n    model_triplet, test_ds_eval, DEVICE)\nquery_feats_tri = extract_query_features(\n    model_triplet, query_ds_eval, DEVICE)\n\nprint(\"Feature extraction complete\")","metadata":{"_uuid":"84c72000-408d-4564-8ea6-d4c5eb4fdf6e","_cell_guid":"00cde330-a579-4304-973a-2386ebf49cf1","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 8. Quantitative Evaluation\n\nI use `eval_search_prw` (adapted from SeqNet, Li et al., 2022) as required by the assignment. A detection counts as a true positive only if IoU > 0.5 with the ground truth AND the identity is correct. `ignore_cam_id=True` following the literature convention (see FAQ).","metadata":{"_uuid":"9a52bbac-4f5a-4d0d-a1b4-3b4db979737a","_cell_guid":"5b162f27-c3f6-4d48-8a7a-63410d4d6213","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"print(\"[Baseline] ResNet-50 + OIM\")\nmAP_base, top1_base, aps_base = eval_search_prw(\n    test_ds_eval, query_ds_eval,\n    gallery_dets_base, gallery_feats_base, query_feats_base,\n    det_thresh=DET_THRESH)\n\nprint(\"\\n[Ablation A] ResNet-18 + OIM\")\nmAP_r18, top1_r18, aps_r18 = eval_search_prw(\n    test_ds_eval, query_ds_eval,\n    gallery_dets_r18, gallery_feats_r18, query_feats_r18,\n    det_thresh=DET_THRESH)\n\nprint(\"\\n[Ablation B] ResNet-50 + Triplet\")\nmAP_tri, top1_tri, aps_tri = eval_search_prw(\n    test_ds_eval, query_ds_eval,\n    gallery_dets_tri, gallery_feats_tri, query_feats_tri,\n    det_thresh=DET_THRESH)","metadata":{"_uuid":"3d460ecf-a820-48d1-9596-22f5f187eb19","_cell_guid":"0216367a-10bb-4bb5-ba66-5672a8e46cbb","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 9. Ablation Study\n\n### Hypotheses\n\n**Ablation A (backbone depth):**\nResNet-18 has fewer residual blocks than ResNet-50, which means less representational capacity at the deepest FPN level. I expect weaker features for both detection (lower recall) and re-identification (less discriminative embeddings), leading to lower mAP and top-1.\n\n**Ablation B (loss function):**\nOIM maintains a lookup table of all 482 training identity prototypes, so each embedding is compared against every known ID at every training step. Triplet loss only contrasts against IDs within the current mini-batch. With 2 images per GPU (4 effective), that is maybe 10-15 unique IDs per step at best. I expect OIM to outperform triplet, especially on mAP.","metadata":{"_uuid":"b037e88c-7ed6-4b5a-a3ed-6e45801065fc","_cell_guid":"656db7a0-c879-47e1-a6aa-e70091c421df","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# table\nprint(f\"{'Model':<30} {'Backbone':<12} {'Loss':<10} {'mAP':>8} {'Top-1':>8}\")\nprint(\"-\" * 70)\nfor name, bb, loss, m, t in [\n    (\"Baseline\", \"ResNet-50\", \"OIM\", mAP_base, top1_base),\n    (\"Ablation A\", \"ResNet-18\", \"OIM\", mAP_r18, top1_r18),\n    (\"Ablation B\", \"ResNet-50\", \"Triplet\", mAP_tri, top1_tri),\n]:\n    print(f\"{name:<30} {bb:<12} {loss:<10} {m*100:>7.1f}% {t*100:>7.1f}%\")\n\n# bar chart\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(11, 4.5))\nlabels = [\"Baseline\\n(R50+OIM)\", \"Ablation A\\n(R18+OIM)\",\n          \"Ablation B\\n(R50+Triplet)\"]\ncolors = [\"#4C72B0\", \"#DD8452\", \"#55A868\"]\nmaps  = [mAP_base * 100, mAP_r18 * 100, mAP_tri * 100]\ntop1s = [top1_base * 100, top1_r18 * 100, top1_tri * 100]\n\nfor ax, vals, metric in zip(axes, [maps, top1s],\n                             [\"mAP (%)\", \"Top-1 Accuracy (%)\"]):\n    bars = ax.bar(labels, vals, color=colors, edgecolor=\"white\", width=0.5)\n    for bar, v in zip(bars, vals):\n        ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, bar.get_height() + 0.3,\n                f\"{v:.1f}%\", ha=\"center\", va=\"bottom\", fontsize=11,\n                fontweight=\"bold\")\n    ax.set_title(metric, fontsize=13)\n    ax.set_ylim(0, max(vals) * 1.25)\n    ax.yaxis.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n    ax.set_axisbelow(True)\n\nplt.suptitle(\"Ablation Study: Person Search on PRW\", fontsize=13, y=1.02)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(\"ablation_results.png\", dpi=130, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\nplt.show()","metadata":{"_uuid":"9ade794b-299a-42cc-9f3d-d18a765a4b27","_cell_guid":"fd3d2684-5b61-4a73-b8d1-5ba64d74d7af","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(14, 4))\nfor ax, (ap_arr, name, color) in zip(axes, [\n        (aps_base, \"Baseline (R50+OIM)\", \"#4C72B0\"),\n        (aps_r18,  \"Ablation A (R18+OIM)\", \"#DD8452\"),\n        (aps_tri,  \"Ablation B (R50+Tri)\", \"#55A868\"),\n    ]):\n    ax.hist(ap_arr, bins=30, color=color, edgecolor=\"white\", alpha=0.85)\n    ax.axvline(np.mean(ap_arr), color=\"red\", linestyle=\"--\",\n               linewidth=1.5, label=f\"mean={np.mean(ap_arr):.3f}\")\n    ax.set_title(name, fontsize=11)\n    ax.set_xlabel(\"AP per Query\")\n    ax.legend(fontsize=9)\n    ax.grid(alpha=0.3)\n\nplt.suptitle(\"Per-Query AP Distribution\", fontsize=13)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(\"ap_distribution.png\", dpi=120, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\nplt.show()","metadata":{"_uuid":"9bc647ee-c5b3-4ef6-88d1-3f269e74256b","_cell_guid":"9c5d8628-65fe-4e7d-a1db-9b0478652835","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### Discussion\n\n**Ablation A (backbone):**\nResNet-18 shows a clear drop in both metrics. The shallower backbone produces weaker features at every FPN level since FPN relies on top-down propagation from the deepest stage. This hurts both detection (lower recall, missed persons especially at small scales) and re-identification (less discriminative embeddings, more confusion between similar-looking people). The AP distribution shifts uniformly leftward, so this is not limited to a few hard queries but is a broad effect.\n\n**Ablation B (loss):**\nThe triplet variant also falls behind OIM. The core issue is batch size. With 2 images per GPU, there are only a handful of unique IDs in each training step. The \"hardest negative\" in such a small pool is unlikely to be globally hard. OIM sidesteps this entirely because the LUT stores prototypes for all 482 IDs, updated via momentum. Every training step effectively contrasts against the full identity space. The circular queue adds further negatives from unlabeled pedestrians.\n\nThese results validate two design choices: (1) deeper backbones are worth the extra compute for this joint task, and (2) OIM is specifically suited for person search because it decouples the number of contrastive identities from the batch size.","metadata":{"_uuid":"1f91f97c-b203-4b20-a9f1-d23bfd9b46de","_cell_guid":"6e966c03-612c-4452-8de1-cd96c2c3037b","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 10. Qualitative Results\n\nBelow I show the top-5 gallery retrievals for several queries. Green borders = correct match (IoU >= 0.5, correct ID). Red = wrong.","metadata":{"_uuid":"5823bff4-635b-4694-85dc-a8278b7032e9","_cell_guid":"81bb2333-90e4-4e3b-9462-42ee69c6f051","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"def _compute_iou_np(a, b):\n    x1 = max(a[0], b[0]); y1 = max(a[1], b[1])\n    x2 = min(a[2], b[2]); y2 = min(a[3], b[3])\n    inter = max(0, x2 - x1) * max(0, y2 - y1)\n    union = (a[2]-a[0])*(a[3]-a[1]) + (b[2]-b[0])*(b[3]-b[1]) - inter\n    return inter / max(union, 1e-6)\n\n\ndef get_topk(gallery_ds, query_ds, g_dets, g_feats, q_feats,\n             qi, k=5, thr=0.5):\n    annos = gallery_ds.annotations\n    ndf = {}\n    for ann, det, feat in zip(annos, g_dets, g_feats):\n        s = det[:, 4].ravel()\n        idx = np.where(s >= thr)[0]\n        if len(idx) > 0:\n            ndf[ann[\"img_name\"]] = (det[idx], feat[idx])\n\n    fp = q_feats[qi].ravel()\n    qa = query_ds.annotations[qi]\n    qpid = qa[\"pids\"]\n    qim = qa[\"img_name\"]\n\n    gt_imgs = {x[\"img_name\"]: x[\"boxes\"][x[\"pids\"] == qpid]\n               for x in annos if qpid in x[\"pids\"] and x[\"img_name\"] != qim}\n\n    sa, ia, ra, la = [], [], [], []\n    for item in annos:\n        gn = item[\"img_name\"]\n        if gn == qim or gn not in ndf:\n            continue\n        det, fg = ndf[gn]\n        fg = fg.reshape(fg.shape[:2])\n        sim = fg.dot(fp).ravel()\n        for s, roi in zip(sim, det):\n            lbl = 0\n            if gn in gt_imgs:\n                gt = gt_imgs[gn].ravel()\n                w, h = gt[2] - gt[0], gt[3] - gt[1]\n                t = min(0.5, w * h / ((w + 10) * (h + 10)))\n                if _compute_iou_np(roi[:4], gt) >= t:\n                    lbl = 1\n            sa.append(s); ia.append(gn); ra.append(roi[:4]); la.append(lbl)\n\n    idx = np.argsort(sa)[::-1][:k]\n    return [(ia[i], ra[i], la[i], sa[i]) for i in idx]\n\n\ndef vis_results(qi, model_name, query_ds, gallery_ds,\n                g_dets, g_feats, q_feats, k=5):\n    topk = get_topk(gallery_ds, query_ds, g_dets, g_feats, q_feats, qi, k)\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, k + 1, figsize=(3 * (k + 1), 5))\n\n    qa = query_ds.annotations[qi]\n    qimg = Image.open(osp.join(query_ds.query_dir, qa[\"img_name\"])).convert(\"RGB\")\n    axes[0].imshow(qimg)\n    axes[0].set_title(f\"QUERY\\nPID {qa['pids']}\", fontsize=10,\n                      fontweight=\"bold\", color=\"#4C72B0\")\n    axes[0].axis(\"off\")\n\n    for rank, (ax, (gn, roi, ok, sc)) in enumerate(zip(axes[1:], topk), 1):\n        gimg = np.array(Image.open(\n            osp.join(gallery_ds.img_prefix, gn)).convert(\"RGB\"))\n        x1, y1, x2, y2 = [int(v) for v in roi]\n        pad = 20\n        crop = gimg[max(0,y1-pad):min(gimg.shape[0],y2+pad),\n                     max(0,x1-pad):min(gimg.shape[1],x2+pad)]\n        c = \"#2ca02c\" if ok else \"#d62728\"\n        ax.imshow(crop)\n        mark = \"CORRECT\" if ok else \"WRONG\"\n        ax.set_title(f\"Rank {rank}\\n{sc:.2f}\\n{mark}\", fontsize=9,\n                     color=c, fontweight=\"bold\")\n        for spine in ax.spines.values():\n            spine.set_edgecolor(c); spine.set_linewidth(3)\n        ax.axis(\"off\")\n\n    plt.suptitle(f\"{model_name} | Query #{qi} (PID {qa['pids']})\", fontsize=12)\n    plt.tight_layout()\n    plt.savefig(f\"qual_q{qi}_{model_name.replace(' ','_')}.png\",\n                dpi=110, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n\n# show results for several queries\nfor qi in [0, 5, 20, 50]:\n    vis_results(qi, \"Baseline (R50+OIM)\", query_ds_eval, test_ds_eval,\n                gallery_dets_base, gallery_feats_base, query_feats_base)\n\n# side-by-side for one query\nprint(\"=== Query #5: Baseline vs. Triplet ===\")\nvis_results(5, \"Baseline (R50+OIM)\", query_ds_eval, test_ds_eval,\n            gallery_dets_base, gallery_feats_base, query_feats_base)\nvis_results(5, \"Ablation B (R50+Triplet)\", query_ds_eval, test_ds_eval,\n            gallery_dets_tri, gallery_feats_tri, query_feats_tri)","metadata":{"_uuid":"5b55ee62-8418-455c-bd1f-e5db75ee37e9","_cell_guid":"4f0406c5-166d-4389-a6b2-b52aefc685c3","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 11. Failure Analysis\n\nUnderstanding when the model fails is as important as knowing when it succeeds. I look at the queries with the lowest AP to identify common failure patterns.","metadata":{"_uuid":"81c76284-e39a-4db8-8f62-224bc9c24165","_cell_guid":"92bfaf6e-8cab-47d3-a360-26148e16b59d","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"sorted_idx = np.argsort(aps_base)\nworst_5 = sorted_idx[:5].tolist()\nbest_5  = sorted_idx[-5:][::-1].tolist()\n\nprint(\"5 Worst Queries (lowest AP):\")\nfor qi in worst_5:\n    ann = query_ds_eval.annotations[qi]\n    print(f\"  Query #{qi:4d}  PID={ann['pids']}  AP={aps_base[qi]:.3f}\")\n\nprint(\"\\n5 Best Queries (highest AP):\")\nfor qi in best_5:\n    ann = query_ds_eval.annotations[qi]\n    print(f\"  Query #{qi:4d}  PID={ann['pids']}  AP={aps_base[qi]:.3f}\")\n\nfor qi in worst_5[:2]:\n    vis_results(qi, \"Baseline [HARD]\", query_ds_eval, test_ds_eval,\n                gallery_dets_base, gallery_feats_base, query_feats_base)","metadata":{"_uuid":"f74662db-9248-4c6a-ae5a-49083a196a62","_cell_guid":"ac76170d-28a0-42ea-ba97-c6d0ba52cbb6","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 12. Conclusions\n\n### Summary of findings\n\n1. **End-to-end training works.** Sharing the backbone between detection and Re-ID lets the two tasks reinforce each other. The features adapt to be simultaneously good for localization and identity discrimination.\n\n2. **OIM is the right loss for this setting.** Its lookup table decouples the number of contrastive identities from the batch size, which is essential when GPU memory forces small batches. Triplet loss suffers from poor negative mining under these constraints.\n\n3. **Backbone depth matters.** ResNet-18 lacks the capacity to produce features rich enough for the joint task. The degradation affects both detection recall and Re-ID accuracy.\n\n4. **Hard cases.** The model struggles with heavy occlusion, very small persons, and clothing ambiguity (multiple people dressed similarly). These are fundamental challenges of the dataset.\n\n### Possible improvements\n\n- Stronger backbones (ResNet-101, Swin Transformer) for richer features.\n- Random Erasing augmentation (Zhong et al., AAAI 2020) for occlusion robustness.\n- CBGM post-processing (Context Bipartite Graph Matching) for spatial co-occurrence.\n- Gradient accumulation to further increase effective batch size.\n\n### DDP experience\n\nUsing DistributedDataParallel on Kaggle's 2x T4 setup roughly halved training time compared to a single GPU. The main consideration is ensuring the sampler is reseeded each epoch and that only rank 0 handles I/O (logging, saving, wandb). For larger-scale experiments, this would scale naturally to more GPUs.","metadata":{"_uuid":"92d29bc4-978a-404e-8a70-429b147c87aa","_cell_guid":"1f4b5359-b9c0-4bed-abfb-a6d29ed62f63","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## References\n\n1. Zheng et al. \"Person Re-identification in the Wild\". CVPR 2017.\n2. Xiao et al. \"Joint Detection and Identification Feature Learning for Person Search\". CVPR 2017.\n3. Li et al. \"SeqNet: Learning Descriptors for Sequence-Based Hierarchical Place Recognition\". RA-L 2022. (eval function adapted from their repo)\n4. Jaffe et al. \"Gallery Filter Network for Person Search\". WACV 2023.\n5. Yu et al. \"Cascade Transformers for End-to-End Person Search\". CVPR 2022.\n6. Hermans et al. \"In Defense of the Triplet Loss for Person Re-Identification\". arXiv 2017.\n7. Zhong et al. \"Random Erasing Data Augmentation\". AAAI 2020.","metadata":{"_uuid":"3b79f741-6799-4234-ace5-7b874c2374b7","_cell_guid":"9441a587-c1cb-43b4-89af-b73ec330d6c5","trusted":true,"collapsed":false,"jupyter":{"outputs_hidden":false}}}]}